dataResourceName: Countryside Council for Wales - Littoral Marine data from Countryside Council for Wales (CCW) Technical Support (Research & Monitoring) Contracts, Wales
dataResourceRights:
Access Constraints: CCW is legally obliged to give public access to the data and information which it holds unless specific legal exceptions apply, for example, if the data is personal or if release of the data would result in environmental harm.

This dataset may certain sensitive species and/or habitats for which detailed location data may be restricted. These include:-
  • King Scallop Pecten maximus (below 20km square)
  • Queen Scallop Aequipecten opercularis (below 20km square)
  • Native Oyster Ostrea edulis (below 20km square)
  • Crayfish Palinurus elephas (below 20km square)
  • Seahorse Hippocampus guttulatus (below 20km square)
  • Short snouted seahorse Hippocampus hippocampus (below 20km square)
  • Grey seal Helichoerus grypus (below 5km square)
  • Harbour porpoise Phocoena phocoena (below 10km square)
  • Bottlenose dolphin Tursiops truncatus (below 10km square)
  • Oyster bed habitat IMX.Ost (biotope code) (below 20km square)
Sensitive data may be made available under licence to approved individuals and organisations on request. Please apply for sensitive access via the Gateway. Use Constraints: There are no use restrictions on this dataset.
